The paper proposes a novel approach to Maximum Likelihood Estimation (MLE) involving approximate inference over latent variables, which is a common problem in machine learning and statistics. The paper specifically focuses on models with a latent structure and partial likelihoods, which are commonly used in Survival Analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.ST (Statistics). The paper also discusses the use of convex conjugates, which is a common technique in Information Theory (cs.IT) and Signal Processing (cs.SI), making these sub-categories also likely.
